Generate a structured career execution timeline based on the candidate's career roadmap phases and transition from {{ current_role }} to {{ target_role }} ({{ experience_level }} level) in {{ target_industry }} over {{ estimated_duration_months }} months.

Candidate Profile Context:
{{ context }}

Roadmap Phases:
{% for phase in roadmap_phases %}
Phase {{ phase.phase_number }}: {{ phase.title }}
Duration: {{ phase.duration }}
Description: {{ phase.description }}
{% endfor %}

Construct a detailed execution timeline. You must return a single JSON object matching this structure:
{
  "weekly_goals": [
    {
      "week_number": 1,
      "goal": "Focus goal for this week",
      "tasks": ["Specific action item 1", "Specific action item 2"]
    }
  ],
  "monthly_milestones": [
    {
      "month_number": 1,
      "milestone": "Focus milestone for this month"
    }
  ],
  "quarterly_objectives": [
    {
      "quarter_number": 1,
      "objective": "Objective to achieve by the end of this quarter"
    }
  ],
  "estimated_completion_date": "Estimated completion date (e.g. within N months from start or specific month/year format)",
  "time_estimates": "Total estimated hours per week or duration summary",
  "dependencies": [
    "Prerequisite skill or task dependency 1",
    "Dependency 2"
  ],
  "priority_ordering": [
    "Priority 1: Description of first priority focus",
    "Priority 2: Description of second priority focus"
  ],
  "milestones": [
    {
      "id": "m1",
      "title": "Milestone Title",
      "description": "Milestone Description",
      "start_week": 1,
      "end_week": 4,
      "estimated_hours": 40,
      "prerequisite_skills": ["Skill A"],
      "expected_outcome": "Demonstrable project or certificate",
      "completion_status": "NOT_STARTED"
    }
  ]
}

Ensure the response contains only the raw, valid JSON object. Do not add markdown backticks, notes, explanations, or code blocks.
